00:29:44,410 --> 00:30:12,747
I've had enough sort of responses from people to begin to perceive that somewhere along the line in the teaching of Vipassana people are not being taught to actually feel their emotions and experience them because I get reports that suddenly something's come up like grief or depression or something and the person didn't know what to do with it you know and then they go to therapy which is fine I mean therapy is very helpful but this is much cheaper and all you've got to do

146
00:30:13,637 --> 00:30:16,560
All you've got to do is just sit with the stuff, right?

147
00:30:16,820 --> 00:30:24,848
That doesn't mean to say that if something comes up very violent, very, you know, where it's actually making you afraid, that you shouldn't seek help, of course you should.

148
00:30:24,868 --> 00:30:40,184
But the healing, the psychological healing, the therapy of vipassana is in the bearing with, is in the sufferance, the open-hearted sufferance of the emotional state that's arising.

149
00:30:40,856 --> 00:31:01,244
and it may be that as you turn inward and you feel your depression and you feel your fear it becomes much greater and that's because you're allowing it to manifest now you're in control of the process all you have to do is stop meditating and have a cup of tea which is the great panacea as you know

150
00:31:04,059 --> 00:31:07,325
So, it's a case of really, really grasping that.

151
00:31:07,345 --> 00:31:11,570
You see, every time, and this is not just in meditation, this is in your daily life.

152
00:31:11,590 --> 00:31:14,654
This is while you're having a cup of tea, while you're watching, you know, while you're talking.

153
00:31:14,674 --> 00:31:19,040
Every time the mind wanders, it's developing a particular attitude.

154
00:31:20,222 --> 00:31:20,442
See?

155
00:31:20,923 --> 00:31:28,755
And when you know that, when you really grasp what you're doing, then, you know, you get more and more, you know, quick about bringing your mind back into the present moment.

156
00:31:30,698 --> 00:31:33,882
And remember, everything you attend to is an act of intention.

157
00:31:34,417 --> 00:31:35,923
You know these billboards on the street?

158
00:31:37,147 --> 00:31:38,112
Why do they still have them?

159
00:31:38,393 --> 00:31:40,400
We've got all sorts of ways of advertising.

160
00:31:40,461 --> 00:31:44,817
Why do they still have these silly billboards all over the street while you're watching on the bus?

161
00:31:45,218 --> 00:32:06,720
years ago there was a doubt as to whether they had any effect whatsoever so I don't know if some of you might remember way back in the 80s actually if I remember rightly early 80s to prove the people who had owned these billboards to prove they worked they introduced this perfume and it was from Australia and it had you know the Australian hat with the corks all around it does anybody remember that?

162
00:32:06,952 --> 00:32:31,037
and it had a special name and everybody thought that's fantastic and everybody wanted to know where it came from it didn't exist what it proved is that every time you look at a billboard it goes in an act of attention is an act of intention it has an effect that's why you don't think so much about what you're going to buy when you walk into the shop you already know the billboards have told you the adverts have told you

163
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:39,046
So, keeping that very clearly in mind, that whatever goes into the mind is conditioning it.

164
00:32:39,686 --> 00:32:44,874
And every time the mind goes off on its little dreams, it's reinforcing that conditioning.

165
00:32:45,714 --> 00:33:01,175
So, there is this instruction from the Buddha to be very careful about what we put into the mind and to practice the virtue of restraint, you see, of not feeding that desire, not feeding...

166
00:33:01,865 --> 00:33:15,502
not feeding into it so that just as a general instruction about what you do when the mind wanders you just come off it you acknowledge exactly what the mind is doing

167
00:33:16,089 --> 00:33:43,701
not in terms of its subject you're not worried about what it's actually doing you're worried about the attitudinal force behind it is it anger, is it depression, whatever it is and you come back into the body you feel it in the body and stay with it as best you can and recognise that that turbulence in the body is actually blowing itself out see that's the point, it's blowing itself out

168
00:33:46,127 --> 00:34:15,713
there's a lot of it and the the other side of the equation is this business of the black hole you see the pit the dullness and lethargy so again that's a mental state we don't tend to think of it like that it's a mental state and it's been developed in two ways first of all we like sleeping especially that one on a Sunday morning where

169
00:34:16,385 --> 00:34:33,072
you sort of wake up and you're on that sort of little level and you sort of just about wake up to get a cup of tea and then you come back down and you lie out and you look at the newspapers and you you know that one?

170
00:34:33,092 --> 00:34:37,380
so that's this lovely subliminal state of sleep which is very pleasant

171
00:34:37,867 --> 00:34:42,755
then you come and sit here you see and you are very still, well what does the mind want to do?

172
00:34:42,896 --> 00:35:01,309
it wants to get into this lovely subliminal state and off it goes so you have to resist that, you have to keep waking up, that's why I say these three basic things about lifting the spine, open the eyes a bit, let the light in, stand up refuse, you see, just refuse to be annihilated, that's the basic, that's the commandment

173
00:35:02,369 --> 00:35:31,818
and the other side of it is that we've used sleep to escape things you know so when you feel a bit fed up feel a bit depressed well you lay out on the couch you know if it gets too bad this neon light comes out doesn't it head for the bed and that's it lay out for a few hours you know and you wake up and it's all been nicely suppressed sometimes it doesn't happen like that you feel even worse but for the most part for the most part we use sleep to suppress remember all suppression is aversion or fear

174
00:35:32,338 --> 00:35:54,228
aversion or fear so that's why in daily life if you have something come up and you know it's the wrong time to deal with it you don't want to be in work telling everybody how depressed you are you can put it to the side your attitude is I'll just put that to the side and deal with it later that's not the same as suppression suppression has to be something negative

175
00:35:54,884 --> 00:35:59,710
And that force is actually adding more turbulence to the system.

176
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:04,818
Whereas just to say, I can't handle it at the moment, and just to leave it to the side, is no danger.

177
00:36:05,277 --> 00:36:11,327
As long as you give it time later on in the day to actually contact it.

178
00:36:11,347 --> 00:36:14,311
So that's the other side of the hindrances.

179
00:36:15,012 --> 00:36:17,635
There's only two actually, dullness and lethargy.

